 for bestpractices and # Landing / Homepage

## Overview
Create a public, marketing-focused Landing / Homepage for Roam Resort that delivers a full-bleed hero experience, clear brand positioning, curated highlighted destinations, editorial teasers, and a prominent primary CTA of “Request a Stay.” The page should maximize visitor engagement, guide authenticated inquiries, and encourage destination browsing. All components must be built with runtime-safe patterns, guard against null/undefined values, and align with the project’s premium editorial aesthetic.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A public marketing landing page that immediately communicates Roam Resort’s luxury, editorial storytelling, and bespoke inquiry-first service. It showcases a full-bleed hero, a succinct brand positioning statement, a carousel of highlighted destinations, editorial teasers, and a primary CTA “Request a Stay” plus a secondary CTA to explore destinations. The page should feel immersive, serene, and high-end.

Goals:
- Convert visitors to authenticated inquirers by presenting a clear path to submit inquiries.
- Encourage browsing destinations through an editorial, editorial-teaser driven experience.
- Provide a visually cohesive entry point into Host and Concierge workflows (via navigation and login prompts) without exposing pricing or booking; emphasize inquiry flow and authentication gate.

Connected features:
- Destination highlights carousel with “View” actions.
- Editorial teaser cards linking to Destination pages.
- Primary CTA “Request a Stay” that routes to the Inquiry flow with authentication gating.
- Top navigation with links to Destinations, About, Help, Login/Signup, Host login.
- Footer with standard policy and social links.

UI elements and visual guidance:
- Hero Section: a full-bleed image or video with a centered, elegant brand positioning line and subline. Primary CTA “Request a Stay” in bronze-gold (#A97C50) and a secondary CTA “Explore Destinations” in soft beige with bronze outline. Ensure the hero supports darkened overlays for readability.
- Navigation: Transparent over hero; on scroll, nav becomes solid bronze-gold underline active state. Mobile: collapsible with smooth slide-out.
- Destination Highlights Carousel: horizontally swipeable or auto-rotating cards with large imagery, titles, short editorial snippets, and a “View” CTA per card.
- Editorial Teasers: grid or horizontal cards with teaser headlines and short summaries linking to Destination pages.
- Footer: policy links (Privacy, Terms), Contact, social icons, and minimal branding.
- Cards: rounded 8–12px, light inner shadow, thin borders in light beige, hover scale and bronze-gold accent border.
- Visual treatments: soft gradients, warm tones, subtle overlays, no harsh grids; maintain editorial luxury feel.
- Accessibility: semantic HTML, alt text for imagery, keyboard navigable carousel, ARIA labels for CTAs.

APIs and data sources:
- Destination data includes: id, name, imageUrl, editorialSnippet, slug, isHighlighted (for arrangement), and link to destination page.
- Editorial teasers data: id, title, excerpt, imageUrl, destinationSlug.
- No external API dependencies required for static MVP; data may be fetched from the existing backend via /api/destinations and /api/editorials if available.
- All data-fetch results must be guarded for nulls and validated as arrays.

## Components to Build
- LandingLayout
  - Props: none or global site theming data
  - Responsibilities: page structure scaffolding, header, hero, sections, footer
- HeroSection
  - Props: backgroundMedia (image or video), title, subtitle, ctas[]
  - Behavior: full-bleed media, overlay, centered copy, responsive.
- NavBar
  - Props: activeSection, userAuthState
  - Behavior: Transparent over hero; switches to solid on scroll; mobile hamburger with slide-out.
- DestinationHighlightsCarousel
  - Props: destinations: DestinationCard[]
  - Subcomponents: DestinationCard
  - Behavior: horizontal scroll/swipe, keyboard navigation, “View” button per card.
- EditorialTeasersGrid
  - Props: teasers: EditorialTeaser[]
  - Subcomponents: EditorialTeaserCard
- CTAButton (reusable)
  - Props: label, variant (primary/secondary), onClick, disabled
  - Styles: bronze-gold fill for primary, soft beige with bronze outline for secondary
